Raspberry Pi 4 — AppImage grid kiosk
====================================

Contents
--------
- lib/appimage_grid_launcher.py — GTK3 grid (~/AppImages + .desktop files)
- bin/rpi-appimage-cage-session — Wayland: Cage + launcher
- bin/rpi-appimage-openbox-session — X11 fallback: Openbox + launcher
- share/wayland-sessions/cage-appimage-grid.desktop — pick this session in lightdm
- share/xsessions/openbox-appimage-grid.desktop — X11 session entry
- share/lightdm/lightdm.conf.d/90-appimage-kiosk.conf.example — autologin snippet
- scripts/setup-user-apps.sh — creates ~/AppImages and sample .desktop

Install on the Pi
-----------------
1. Copy this `rpi-appimage-launcher` folder to the Pi (e.g. under your home directory).

2. Install packages (Raspberry Pi OS Bookworm, 64-bit):
   sudo apt update
   sudo apt install -y cage python3-gi gir1.2-gtk-3.0 dbus-x11

   Optional X11 fallback:
   sudo apt install -y openbox

3. Run the installer (does not need the execute bit; use sh):
   sh rpi-appimage-launcher/install.sh

4. Per-user directories and sample desktop entry:
   sh rpi-appimage-launcher/scripts/setup-user-apps.sh

5. Put aarch64 AppImages in ~/AppImages and mark executable:
   chmod +x ~/AppImages/*.AppImage

6. Autologin into the grid (lightdm):
   sudo cp rpi-appimage-launcher/share/lightdm/lightdm.conf.d/90-appimage-kiosk.conf.example \
     /etc/lightdm/lightdm.conf.d/90-appimage-kiosk.conf
   Edit the file: set autologin-user to your username. Keep autologin-session=cage-appimage-grid
   unless you use the Openbox session (openbox-appimage-grid).
   sudo systemctl restart lightdm

Launcher usage
--------------
- Refresh: F5 or Refresh button
- Exit launcher (maintenance): Ctrl+Shift+Q
- Window close is ignored in kiosk mode; rely on the key chord above

Environment
-----------
- RPI_APPIMAGE_LAUNCHER — override path to appimage_grid_launcher.py (for development)

Cage and multiple windows
-------------------------
Launched AppImages appear as additional windows; use Cage’s window switching (see cage(1),
often Alt+Escape / Alt+Tab depending on build) to return to the grid.
